Flatbush Ave., east side, south of Tilden Ave., showing the Van Beuren home. In 1850 it was known as the Jacob Duryea house, and was midw y between Cortelyou Road (then Canarsie Lane), and Tilden Ave., (then Vernon Ave). The property was acquired by the B-ooklyn City R.R. Co., whose carbarns appear to the right of the house.
1892.
Eugene L. Armbruster Cellection.
